article_text:
Despite continued weak employment data and gridlock in Washington, consumers are showing surprising signs of confidence, and opening their wallets to buy big-ticket items ranging from washing machines to fast boats.

U.S. shipments of home appliances continued growing, helping double third-quarter profit at Whirlpool Corp. as stronger U.S. housing sales offset weakness in much of the world. North America's largest appliance maker...
